&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Administration Resilience Team - Staff Bank (Band 2/3 dependent upon experience)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours&lt;/strong&gt;: variable hours working for the staff bank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base:&lt;/strong&gt; There are 13 neighbourhood teams providing services across Leeds and our trust headquarters so your assignment will be dependent upon the needs of the services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you want to join our Administration Resilience Team? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We need your help in maintaining important health services. In return we can provide opportunities for you to work in many of our services. You will be a vital part of a flexible team which supports our nursing and healthcare teams to continue providing excellent patient care to the people of Leeds.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We need people who can work at short notice, can cover adhoc shifts and who have a passion for helping their community. You will have excellent customer service, sound working knowledge of Microsoft Office and ideally have some administration experience or transferrable skills you can put into use.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are many benefits to joining our temporary bank. We cannot guarantee work but we can offer you flexibility, some longer term assignments, development, support and access to specialist training to further develop your skills and expertise. This may also be an opportunity for you to decide whether you want to apply for a more permanent role with the trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel like we&#39;re the place for you to make a difference then start your application now. To find out more about working at Leeds Community Healthcare then head to our website.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please can you state your availability for work in your application form. We would like to know if you are available for full time/part time/weekends/evenings or ad-hoc shifts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
